{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01WRTrKbaZ8YYqCHjshj73R6","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The Prometheus CR is configured to:\n- `serviceMonitorNamespaceSelector: matchNames: [cockroachdb]` - it will look for ServiceMonitors in the `cockroachdb` namespace\n- `serviceMonitorSelector: {}` - selects all ServiceMonitors (empty selector = match all)\n- `podMonitorNamespaceSelector: matchNames: [cockroachdb]` - it will look for PodMonitors in the `cockroachdb` namespace\n- `podMonitorSelector: {}` - selects all PodMonitors\n\nThe CockroachDB service `crdb-cluster` has:\n- Port `http` on 8080 for metrics\n- Labels including `app.kubernetes.io/name: cockroachdb`, `app.kubernetes.io/instance: crdb-cluster`, and `app.kubernetes.io/component: database`\n\nI need to create a ServiceMonitor in the `cockroachdb` namespace that targets this service on port 8080 at the `/_status/vars` path, with a selector matching the service labels.\n\nSince the Prometheus instance has `serviceMonitorSelector: {}`, it will pick up any ServiceMonitor in the allowed namespaces, so I don't need specific labels on the ServiceMonitor itself. I should also verify that Prometheus has the necessary RBAC permissions to access the cockroachdb namespace.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1391,"cache_read_input_tokens":30137,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1391},"output_tokens":22,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c388d5ea-3412-4628-988d-9b5dfe340461","uuid":"c2f3a36c-adec-4911-950e-0c40cc377845","request_id":"req_011Ccc1nnWYAXXyuQDp3GRiS"}
